      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Circle of Fifths is a visual chart that maps out all 12 musical notes and their relative keys, showing how they are related through major and minor triads. It helps you figure out a song's key by identifying the key signature (the number of sharps or flats) on the staff and matching it to the corresponding position on the circle. For example, if a song has two sharps, you look for the \"two sharps\" spot on the circle to find the key of A Major or F# Minor. You can also use the circle to determine the relative minor key by moving two steps clockwise or counter-clockwise from the major key. By practicing this pattern, you'll quickly recognize the tonal centers of different songs without needing to analyze every note individually.",
