      "content": "The name comes from the fact that moving clockwise around the circle adds a perfect fifth to the previous note, which is a specific interval of seven semitones. Mathematically, this relationship creates a repeating cycle because stacking fifths eventually brings you back to the starting pitch class after going around twelve times. Because a perfect fifth is the most consonant interval in Western music, it became the foundational building block for organizing keys and scales. This pattern allows musicians to see how keys are related by this specific intervallic step rather than just arbitrary ordering.",
